<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="a12Jul1936"><font color="red">12 July 1936</font> <i>NLHW</i> (from Paul L&eacute;on to Harriet Weaver): The great problem has been and still is Mr Joyce&apos;s daughter &hellip; one copy of her book for her birthday &hellip; One of its results anyhow has been that Mr Joyce had the visit here of a viscount Carlow who has a hobby in printing and who wants to bring out a small fragment of Wip with lettrines by Lucia. The fragment for want of a better text is the last one which appeared in Transition  </div>
